name: INStartCallIntentHandling
desc: An interface that handles requests to start audio and video calls.

items.name: func resolveCallCapability(for: INStartCallIntent, with: (INStartCallCallCapabilityResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the type of call to start.

items.name: func resolveContacts(for: INStartCallIntent, with: ([INStartCallContactResolutionResult]) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the recipients of the call.

items.name: func resolveDestinationType(for: INStartCallIntent, with: (INCallDestinationTypeResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the destination of the call.

items.name: func resolveCallRecordToCallBack(for: INStartCallIntent, with: (INCallRecordResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the redial of a missed call.

items.name: func confirm(intent: INStartCallIntent, completion: (INStartCallIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Confirms whether your app is able to initiate the call.

items.name: func handle(intent: INStartCallIntent, completion: (INStartCallIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Handles handing off the call to your app.
